                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.029,
                                "byte_start": 109568,
                                "byte_stop": 153767,
                                "text": "In the 1930s, Congress responded to the need of senior citizens for old-age and survivors\u0027 insurance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 11.029,
                                "stop": 19.069,
                                "byte_start": 153767,
                                "byte_stop": 185846,
                                "text": "It did so by making social security, a tax based entirely federal program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.069,
                                "stop": 28.882,
                                "byte_start": 185846,
                                "byte_stop": 225134,
                                "text": "In 2010, Congress addressed the public\u0027s need for affordable health care when sickness or injury occurs."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 28.882,
                                "stop": 39.266,
                                "byte_start": 225134,
                                "byte_stop": 266721,
                                "text": "Congress did so by taking a path unlike the one it took for social security instead of an entirely federal program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.266,
                                "stop": 50.038,
                                "byte_start": 266721,
                                "byte_stop": 309770,
                                "text": "The Affordable Health Care Act gives states and private insurers important roles in insuring medical care for those who need it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.038,
                                "stop": 59.491,
                                "byte_start": 309770,
                                "byte_stop": 347596,
                                "text": "The question the Court must answer is whether the Constitution stops Congress from taking the course it did."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.491,
                                "stop": 64.171,
                                "byte_start": 347596,
                                "byte_stop": 366299,
                                "text": "I would answer emphatically no."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.171,
                                "stop": 80.398,
                                "byte_start": 366299,
                                "byte_stop": 431188,
                                "text": "I agree with the Chief Justice that Congress\u0027 power to tax and spend supports the so-called individual mandate or minimum coverage provision, but I would make that an auxiliary holding."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.398,
                                "stop": 93.611,
                                "byte_start": 431188,
                                "byte_stop": 484059,
                                "text": "As I see it, Congress\u0027 vast authority to regulate interstate commerce solidly undergirds the affordable health care legislation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.611,
                                "stop": 99.953,
                                "byte_start": 484059,
                                "byte_stop": 509450,
                                "text": "I would uphold the legislation first and foremost on that ground."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.953,
                                "stop": 111.939,
                                "byte_start": 509450,
                                "byte_stop": 557411,
                                "text": "Since 1937, this Court has deferred, as it should, to Congress\u0027 policymaking in the economic and social realm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.939,
                                "stop": 119.186,
                                "byte_start": 557411,
                                "byte_stop": 586355,
                                "text": "Today, a majority of the Court rules that the Commerce Clause is not equal to the task."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.186,
                                "stop": 137.32,
                                "byte_start": 586355,
                                "byte_stop": 658871,
                                "text": "That ruling harks back to the era ended 75 years ago when the Court routinely thwarted legislative efforts to regulate the economy in the interest of those who labor to sustain it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.32,
                                "stop": 141.453,
                                "byte_start": 658871,
                                "byte_stop": 675485,
                                "text": "It is a stunning setback."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 141.453,
                                "stop": 146.392,
                                "byte_start": 675485,
                                "byte_stop": 695233,
                                "text": "It should not have staying power."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.392,
                                "stop": 155.563,
                                "byte_start": 695233,
                                "byte_stop": 731909,
                                "text": "The Court\u0027s majority would compare health insurance to any other commodity, broccoli for example."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 155.563,
                                "stop": 162.67,
                                "byte_start": 731909,
                                "byte_stop": 760330,
                                "text": "If the Government can compel people to buy insurance, then there was no commodity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.67,
                                "stop": 177.516,
                                "byte_start": 760330,
                                "byte_stop": 819681,
                                "text": "The Government can\u0027t force people to purchase, so the argument goes, but health care is not like vegetables or other items one is at liberty to buy or not to buy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.516,
                                "stop": 189.617,
                                "byte_start": 819681,
                                "byte_stop": 868059,
                                "text": "All of us will need health care, some sooner, some later, but we can\u0027t tell when, where or how dire our need will be."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 189.617,
                                "stop": 205.675,
                                "byte_start": 868059,
                                "byte_stop": 932321,
                                "text": "A healthy 21-year-old, for example, may tomorrow be the victim of an accident that leaves him or her an invalid, in need of constant and costly medical care."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 205.675,
                                "stop": 212.675,
                                "byte_start": 932321,
                                "byte_stop": 960324,
                                "text": "Further, to get broccoli, one must pay at the counter, not so of health care."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 212.675,
                                "stop": 236.02,
                                "byte_start": 960324,
                                "byte_stop": 1053738,
                                "text": "The accident victim who cannot pay the steep price of medical services will nevertheless receive emergency and follow-up care because the law and professional ethics so require and because ours is a humane society, but people who do purchase insurance end up footing the bill."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 236.02,
                                "stop": 247.212,
                                "byte_start": 1053738,
                                "byte_stop": 1098459,
                                "text": "By requiring the healthy uninsured either to obtain insurance or pay a toll, Congress sought to end this free ride."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 247.212,
                                "stop": 262.428,
                                "byte_start": 1098459,
                                "byte_stop": 1159377,
                                "text": "It is shortsighted moreover to see the mandate as a decree that the hale and hearty young people subsidize care rendered to older, less healthy people."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 262.428,
                                "stop": 270.646,
                                "byte_start": 1159377,
                                "byte_stop": 1192187,
                                "text": "In the fullness of time, today\u0027s young and healthy will become society\u0027s old and infirm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 270.646,
                                "stop": 277.207,
                                "byte_start": 1192187,
                                "byte_stop": 1218414,
                                "text": "Viewed over a lifespan, the cost and benefits even out."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 277.207,
                                "stop": 291.855,
                                "byte_start": 1218414,
                                "byte_stop": 1277032,
                                "text": "And as I just observed, the youth who does not want insurance today may find that tomorrow she desperately needs the services insurance is designed to secure."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 291.855,
                                "stop": 313.175,
                                "byte_start": 1277032,
                                "byte_stop": 1362296,
                                "text": "What the mandate does essentially is to require people to prepay for medical care to insurance instead of waiting, expecting to pay out-of-pocket at the point of service when in reality many will lack the money to cover the cost."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 313.175,
                                "stop": 327.531,
                                "byte_start": 1362296,
                                "byte_stop": 1419766,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice reasons that Congress can use its commerce power to regulate something already in existence, but cannot create that something in order to regulate it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 327.531,
                                "stop": 333.557,
                                "byte_start": 1419766,
                                "byte_stop": 1443798,
                                "text": "But the interstate health insurance and health care markets are not Congress\u0027 creations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 333.557,
                                "stop": 340.095,
                                "byte_start": 1443798,
                                "byte_stop": 1470025,
                                "text": "Both existed well before the enactment of the Affordable HealthCare Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 340.095,
                                "stop": 367.482,
                                "byte_start": 1470025,
                                "byte_stop": 1579530,
                                "text": "I have already emphasized the unique attributes of the health care market, the fact that all of us will be in it sooner or later and cannot predict exactly when the huge free ride, a problem caused by people who refrain from purchasing insurance then become sick or injured and get care cost free to them but costly for those of us who have paid in advance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 367.482,
                                "stop": 382.52,
                                "byte_start": 1579530,
                                "byte_stop": 1639717,
                                "text": "Because there is no comparable market, the slippery slope envisioned by the Court\u0027s majority, if health insurance today then broccoli tomorrow, is far more imaginary than real."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 382.52,
                                "stop": 390.37,
                                "byte_start": 1639717,
                                "byte_stop": 1671064,
                                "text": "As a learned jurist once commented, judges and lawyers live on the slippery slope of analogies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 390.37,
                                "stop": 394.382,
                                "byte_start": 1671064,
                                "byte_stop": 1687155,
                                "text": "They are not supposed to skid to the bottom."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 394.382,
                                "stop": 402.36,
                                "byte_start": 1687155,
                                "byte_stop": 1719024,
                                "text": "Yes, the insurance purchase mandate is novel, but novelty is no reason to reject it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 402.36,
                                "stop": 413.835,
                                "byte_start": 1719024,
                                "byte_stop": 1765000,
                                "text": "As our economy grows and changes, Congress must be competent to devise legislation meeting current day social and economic realities."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 413.835,
                                "stop": 430.656,
                                "byte_start": 1765000,
                                "byte_stop": 1832291,
                                "text": "For that reason, the Necessary and Proper Clause was included in the Constitution to ensure that the Federal Government would have the capacity to provide for conditions and developments, the framers knew they could scarcely foresee."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 430.656,
                                "stop": 445.372,
                                "byte_start": 1832291,
                                "byte_stop": 1891119,
                                "text": "In enacting the Affordable Health Care Act, Congress\u0027 aim was to reduce the large numbers of U.S. residents, some 50 million in 2009, who lacked health insurance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 445.372,
                                "stop": 458.062,
                                "byte_start": 1891119,
                                "byte_stop": 1941901,
                                "text": "Congress was aware that the vast majority of those people lack insurance not by choice."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 458.062,
                                "stop": 466.122,
                                "byte_start": 1941901,
                                "byte_stop": 1974084,
                                "text": "One group of particular concern to Congress were individuals with preexisting medical conditions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 466.122,
                                "stop": 476.447,
                                "byte_start": 1974084,
                                "byte_stop": 2015357,
                                "text": "Before the Affordable Health Care Act\u0027s enactment, the insurance industry charged these individuals steep prices or flatly denied them coverage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 476.447,
                                "stop": 493.877,
                                "byte_start": 2015357,
                                "byte_stop": 2085157,
                                "text": "Congress understood, however, that a simple ban on those practices would not work without the mandate to -- to acquire insurance covering those with preexisting conditions would trigger a death spiral in the heath insurance market."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 493.877,
                                "stop": 515.323,
                                "byte_start": 2085157,
                                "byte_stop": 2170943,
                                "text": "Many people would not buy insurance until they suffered sickness or injury, premiums would skyrocket, more people would be added to the ranks of the uninsured because they could not pay the steep premiums and eventually, insurance companies left with a pool of high risk policyholders would exit the market."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 515.323,
                                "stop": 518.489,
                                "byte_start": 2170943,
                                "byte_stop": 2183586,
                                "text": "With the mandate, the job could be done."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 518.489,
                                "stop": 527.563,
                                "byte_start": 2183586,
                                "byte_stop": 2219844,
                                "text": "Access to insurance would be available and affordable and uncompensated care would be hugely reduced."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 527.563,
                                "stop": 531.403,
                                "byte_start": 2219844,
                                "byte_stop": 2235204,
                                "text": "In no way was Congress\u0027 action improper."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 531.403,
                                "stop": 534.442,
                                "byte_start": 2235204,
                                "byte_stop": 2247429,
                                "text": "The mandate acts directly on individuals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 534.442,
                                "stop": 538.554,
                                "byte_start": 2247429,
                                "byte_stop": 2263834,
                                "text": "It does not commandeer the States as intermediaries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 538.554,
                                "stop": 548.698,
                                "byte_start": 2263834,
                                "byte_stop": 2304376,
                                "text": "And along with other provisions of the Act, it addresses the sort of country-wide problem that made the Commerce Clause essential."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 548.698,
                                "stop": 558.727,
                                "byte_start": 2304376,
                                "byte_stop": 2344500,
                                "text": "The crisis created by the many millions of U.S. residents who lack health insurance is hardly contained within state boundaries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 558.727,
                                "stop": 572.618,
                                "byte_start": 2344500,
                                "byte_stop": 2400089,
                                "text": "Far from encroaching on state prerogatives, the Affordable Health Care Act supplies a better response to remedy the States acting separately are incapable of meeting."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 572.618,
                                "stop": 582.938,
                                "byte_start": 2400089,
                                "byte_stop": 2441362,
                                "text": "This Court has long recognized that the power to regulate interstate commerce is an affirmative power commensurate with national needs."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 582.938,
                                "stop": 594.002,
                                "byte_start": 2441362,
                                "byte_stop": 2485666,
                                "text": "While the Court upholds the mandate, as it surely should, it also regrettably helms in Congress\u0027 commerce power."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 594.002,
                                "stop": 602.968,
                                "byte_start": 2485666,
                                "byte_stop": 2521506,
                                "text": "In doing so, the Court invites assaults on national legislation irreconcilable with the framers\u0027 anticipation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 602.968,
                                "stop": 625.007,
                                "byte_start": 2521506,
                                "byte_stop": 2609695,
                                "text": "Their understanding and expectation was that the Commerce Clause would empower Congress to act in all cases for the general interest of the Union and also in those instances in which the States are separately incompetent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 625.007,
                                "stop": 634.563,
                                "byte_start": 2609695,
                                "byte_stop": 2647834,
                                "text": "My dissent from the Court\u0027s retrogressive reading of the Commerce Clause is joined by Justices Breyer, Sotomayor and Kagan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 634.563,
                                "stop": 645.011,
                                "byte_start": 2647834,
                                "byte_stop": 2689630,
                                "text": "There is a further issue; Congress\u0027 expansion of Medicaid to include a larger portion of the Nation\u0027s poor."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 645.011,
                                "stop": 651.602,
                                "byte_start": 2689630,
                                "byte_stop": 2716066,
                                "text": "Medicaid is the prototypical example of federal-state cooperation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 651.602,
                                "stop": 675.692,
                                "byte_start": 2716066,
                                "byte_stop": 2812406,
                                "text": "Rather than authorizing a federal agency to administer a uniform national health care system for the poor, as Congress did in establishing Medicare for seniors, Congress offered States the opportunity to tailor Medicaid grants to their particular needs so long as they remain within bounds set by the federal law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 675.692,
                                "stop": 694.036,
                                "byte_start": 2812406,
                                "byte_stop": 2885757,
                                "text": "Congress reserved the right to alter, amend or repeal any and every provision of the Medicaid Act and participating States for their part agreed to amend their Medicaid plans consistent with alterations in the federal law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 694.036,
                                "stop": 706.83,
                                "byte_start": 2885757,
                                "byte_stop": 2936957,
                                "text": "From 1965 until 2010, States regularly conformed to amendments expanding Medicaid, sometimes quite sizably."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 706.83,
                                "stop": 713.242,
                                "byte_start": 2936957,
                                "byte_stop": 2962557,
                                "text": "The 2010 expansion is different in kind the Court concludes 7-to-2."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 713.242,
                                "stop": 719.504,
                                "byte_start": 2962557,
                                "byte_stop": 2987635,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor and I strongly disagree."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 719.504,
                                "stop": 722.784,
                                "byte_start": 2987635,
                                "byte_stop": 3000801,
                                "text": "According to the Chief Justice, the expansion was misnamed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 722.784,
                                "stop": 746.759,
                                "byte_start": 3000801,
                                "byte_stop": 3096618,
                                "text": "It did not expand Medicaid as it existed in 2010 he maintains instead Congress established a wholly new program alongside old Medicaid and coerced the States to accept new Medicaid by threatening them with loss of funds from the old program if they hold out."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 746.759,
                                "stop": 759.295,
                                "byte_start": 3096618,
                                "byte_stop": 3146773,
                                "text": "On this reasoning, the Court, for the first time ever, finds an exercise of Congress\u0027 spending power unconstitutionally coercive."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 759.295,
                                "stop": 771.019,
                                "byte_start": 3146773,
                                "byte_stop": 3193689,
                                "text": "In truth, however, Medicaid is a single program with one constant aim to enable poor persons to receive basic health care when they need it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 771.019,
                                "stop": 774.585,
                                "byte_start": 3193689,
                                "byte_stop": 3208004,
                                "text": "What the expansion does is simply this."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 774.585,
                                "stop": 783.292,
                                "byte_start": 3208004,
                                "byte_stop": 3242799,
                                "text": "It adds more people, all of them poor, to the Medicaid eligible population."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 783.292,
                                "stop": 789.029,
                                "byte_start": 3242799,
                                "byte_stop": 3265787,
                                "text": "Congress did not otherwise change the operation of the program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 789.029,
                                "stop": 795.021,
                                "byte_start": 3265787,
                                "byte_stop": 3289715,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice justifies his characterization of the expansion as a new program on three grounds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 795.021,
                                "stop": 814.756,
                                "byte_start": 3289715,
                                "byte_stop": 3368605,
                                "text": "First, he says, by covering those earning up to 133% of the federal poverty line, the expansion, unlike Medicaid as originality enacted, does not care for the neediest among us."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 814.756,
                                "stop": 821.838,
                                "byte_start": 3368605,
                                "byte_stop": 3396921,
                                "text": "The expansion covers individuals earning less than $15,000 annually."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 821.838,
                                "stop": 828.688,
                                "byte_start": 3396921,
                                "byte_stop": 3424402,
                                "text": "Those low earners, on any fair assessment, ranked among the Nation\u0027s poor."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 828.688,
                                "stop": 839.057,
                                "byte_start": 3424402,
                                "byte_stop": 3465885,
                                "text": "Second, the Chief observes that newly eligible people receive a level of coverage less comprehensive than the traditional Medicaid package."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 839.057,
                                "stop": 844.382,
                                "byte_start": 3465885,
                                "byte_stop": 3487201,
                                "text": "But the Affordable Health Care Act did not introduce the less comprehensive package."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 844.382,
                                "stop": 853.453,
                                "byte_start": 3487201,
                                "byte_stop": 3523459,
                                "text": "Since 2006, states had been free to use it for many of their Medicaid beneficiaries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 853.453,
                                "stop": 857.753,
                                "byte_start": 3523459,
                                "byte_stop": 3540595,
                                "text": "Third, the reimbursement rate for participating States is different."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 857.753,
                                "stop": 868.32,
                                "byte_start": 3540595,
                                "byte_stop": 3582913,
                                "text": "True, but that rate is markedly more generous than the usual federal contribution, hardly something the States can complain about."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 868.32,
                                "stop": 876.337,
                                "byte_start": 3582913,
                                "byte_stop": 3614992,
                                "text": "The Federal Government picks up 100% of the tab initially gradually reducing to 90%."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 876.337,
                                "stop": 902.161,
                                "byte_start": 3614992,
                                "byte_stop": 3718228,
                                "text": "Suppose Congress had, from the start, made Medicaid eligible all those originally covered plus those added by the expansion, that would be unobjectionable under the Chief Justice\u0027s reasoning, but we have never held that a grant program becomes two rather one when Congress lays a foundation and later lose on it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 902.161,
                                "stop": 914.896,
                                "byte_start": 3718228,
                                "byte_stop": 3769219,
                                "text": "Congress can and often does expand programs adding new conditions that grant recipients must meet in order to continue receiving funds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 914.896,
                                "stop": 936.879,
                                "byte_start": 3769219,
                                "byte_stop": 3857095,
                                "text": "Our decision, I acknowledge -- our decisions have hypothesized that a financial inducement might pass the point where a pressure becomes coercion and therefore exceed Congress\u0027 spending power, but until today, that prospect has remained theoretical."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 936.879,
                                "stop": 941.803,
                                "byte_start": 3857095,
                                "byte_stop": 3876843,
                                "text": "The Court had found no case fitting the bill."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 941.803,
                                "stop": 954.9,
                                "byte_start": 3876843,
                                "byte_stop": 3929192,
                                "text": "Recall that Congress reserved to itself, when it adopted Medicaid in 1965, the right to alter, amend, even repeal any and every provision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 954.9,
                                "stop": 958.824,
                                "byte_start": 3929192,
                                "byte_stop": 3944866,
                                "text": "This Court long ago explained just what those words mean."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 958.824,
                                "stop": 972.14,
                                "byte_start": 3944866,
                                "byte_stop": 3998156,
                                "text": "They mean Congress retains full and complete power to make such alterations and amendments as come within the just scope of the legislative power."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 972.14,
                                "stop": 974.948,
                                "byte_start": 3998156,
                                "byte_stop": 4009441,
                                "text": "States have not missed that meaning."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 974.948,
                                "stop": 996.817,
                                "byte_start": 4009441,
                                "byte_stop": 4096899,
                                "text": "Each time a State notified the Federal Government of a change it made in its own Medicaid plan, it certified both that it knew the federally set terms of participations could change and that it would abide by the changes as a condition of continued participation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 996.817,
                                "stop": 1005.325,
                                "byte_start": 4096899,
                                "byte_stop": 4130962,
                                "text": "Today\u0027s decision holds that Congress can alter a spending program somewhat, but not too much."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1005.325,
                                "stop": 1017.203,
                                "byte_start": 4130962,
                                "byte_stop": 4178401,
                                "text": "We can anticipate bolder challenges than in the past urging that a congressional amendment goes too far turning pressure into compulsion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1017.203,
                                "stop": 1039.636,
                                "byte_start": 4178401,
                                "byte_stop": 4268157,
                                "text": "When those challenges arrive, my colleagues may comprehend the wisdom of the observation that conceptions of impermissible coercion premised on a State\u0027s perceived inability to decline federal funds are just too amorphous to be judicially administrable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1039.636,
                                "stop": 1052.331,
                                "byte_start": 4268157,
                                "byte_stop": 4318939,
                                "text": "At bottom, my colleagues\u0027 position is that the States\u0027 reliance on federal funds limits Congress\u0027 authority to alter its spending programs."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1052.331,
                                "stop": 1055.456,
                                "byte_start": 4318939,
                                "byte_stop": 4331478,
                                "text": "This gets things backward."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1055.456,
                                "stop": 1074.006,
                                "byte_start": 4331478,
                                "byte_stop": 4405666,
                                "text": "Congress, not the States, is tasked by the Constitution with spending federal money in service of their general welfare and each successive Congress is empowered to appropriate funds as it sees fit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1074.006,
                                "stop": 1099.098,
                                "byte_start": 4405666,
                                "byte_stop": 4505976,
                                "text": "When the 111th Congress reached a conclusion about the portion of the Nation\u0027s poor that should qualify for Medicaid apportioned larger than a predecessor Congress covered, the later Congress abridged no States\u0027 right to existing or preexisting funds for in truth there are no such funds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1099.098,
                                "stop": 1109.534,
                                "byte_start": 4505976,
                                "byte_stop": 4547772,
                                "text": "It is only money the States anticipate receiving, but can scarcely insist on receiving from future Congresses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1109.534,
                                "stop": 1120.201,
                                "byte_start": 4547772,
                                "byte_stop": 4590404,
                                "text": "Seven Members of the Court, however, buy the argument that prospective withholding of anticipated funds exceeds Congress\u0027 spending power."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1120.201,
                                "stop": 1126.538,
                                "byte_start": 4590404,
                                "byte_stop": 4615795,
                                "text": "Given that holding, I entirely agree with the Chief Justice as to the appropriate remedy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1126.538,
                                "stop": 1134.856,
                                "byte_start": 4615795,
                                "byte_stop": 4649023,
                                "text": "It is to bar the withholding found impermissible not to scrap the expansion altogether."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1134.856,
                                "stop": 1149.207,
                                "byte_start": 4649023,
                                "byte_stop": 4706492,
                                "text": "This Court has many times explained that when it confirms a statute marred by a constitutional infirmity, its endeavor must be to salvage, not demolish the legislation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1149.207,
                                "stop": 1161.031,
                                "byte_start": 4706492,
                                "byte_stop": 4753721,
                                "text": "The Court does that by declaring the statute invalid to the extent it reaches too far, but otherwise leaving the statute intact."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1161.031,
                                "stop": 1183.106,
                                "byte_start": 4753721,
                                "byte_stop": 4842015,
                                "text": "Because the Court finds the withholding, not the granting of federal funds, incompatible with the Spending Clause, Congress\u0027 extension of Medicaid remains available to any State affirming its willingness to accept the uncommonly generous federal grant."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1183.106,
                                "stop": 1198.206,
                                "byte_start": 4842015,
                                "byte_stop": 4902410,
                                "text": "So, in the end, the Affordable Health Care Act survives largely unscathed, but the Court\u0027s Commerce and Spending Clause jurisprudence has been set array."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 1198.206,
                                "stop": 1208.607,
                                "byte_start": 4902410,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "My expectation is that the setbacks will be temporary glyphs, not permanent obstructions."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
